Fixes #4 DupFilter and DupPreventFilter is now case insensitive for both HEADERS and QUERY_STRING, where they used to work only for QUERY_STRING because of a to_upper that is done when arguments are split, but headers' case is preserved, so now making the multimap case insensitive renders both OK at the cost of slightly slower searches, however the impact should be minor for ~10 headers and ~10 query string params
add support for DupApplicationScope METHOD to duplicate based on http method PATCH/POST/GET. Nonreg and unit tests included prevent from using a non raw filter in cases where it could not match

all global apache conf settings can now only be set in VirtualHost or Server config to prevent unexpected issues improve non-reg, now properly answers something to dup error is logged in case of HTTP status != 200, not only on curl error
add targets install_* add IfModule in apache conf files update README
add DupErrorLogBodyMatch functionality to print a subset of the body in case of dup error improve debug logs by printing curl reason instead of code
faster exit in case multiple dups are performed for one request: only the running curl can block, no more need to wait until the poison pill split MultiThreadQueue into header and implem cc
move ThreadPool code to cc file
add capacity to duplicate up to 10 times per destination (1000%) fix loglevel comparison for print to stdout (useful for unit tests) improve unit coverage

improve X_DUP_LOG output with the curl status code in case of failure, this might help correcting destinations add body in error log, so that user ids or requests can be replayed easier when failed. beware that logs are truncated based on your syslog config (1024 by default)
change HeaderList into CompareHeader and BodyList into CompareBody for easier doc add CompareLogType archive to replace DisableLibwsdiff

fix double UNIQUE_ID set by compare improve X_DUP_LOG content for debugging when it does not duplicate, it tells you how many filters were configured, so you known if you're hitting the proper path/conf return error on apache start if DupDestination is missing,
fix issue #2 now cmake tries to link with pns_jsoncpp and falls back to jsoncpp if not found

start to improve doc add ApplicationScope URL_AND_HEADERS, rename HEADER -> HEADERS. Scopes are now understandable as-is. fix unit test and long overdue functional tests fix mock to be resistant to chunked and compressed data

avoid infinite loop when duplicating to localhost or loop in your dup network improve debugability when using X_DUP_LOG: compare answers which dir conf it uses and where the diffs are logged
